title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: R package tscompdata provides time series data following forecasting competitions: M, M3, NN3, NN5, NNGC1, Tourism GEFCom2012. M, M3 Tourism data loaded Mcomp Tcomp packages. remaining data contained within tscompdata package.

title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: Data NN3 forecasting competition, comprising 111 monthly time series class ts. Training test data combined. competition, last 18 months used test data. Time series NN3-101 NN3-111 made reduced data set competition.
code: head(nn3[[1]]) #>       Jan  Feb  Mar  Apr  May  Jun #> 1990 5520 3940 4490 5030 5660 4790 autoplot(nn3[[1]])

title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: Data NN5 forecasting competition, comprising 111 daily time series lass msts. Training test data combined. competition, last 56 days used test data. Time series NN5-101 NN5-111 made reduced data set competition.
code: head(nn3[[2]]) #>       Jan  Feb  Mar  Apr  May  Jun #> 1990 5080 3690 4260 3920 4290 3840 autoplot(nn5[[2]])

title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: Data NNGC1 forecasting competition, comprising 11 annual time series, 11 quarterly time series, 11 monthly time series, 11 weekly time series, 11 daily time series 11 hourly time series class ts msts. training data provided.

title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: Data GEFCOM2012 forecasting competition hosted kaggle platform. data comprise 20 time series containing hourly load data 20 zones United States, class msts. training data provided. missing data series formed test sets.
code: head(gefcom2012_load[[4]]) #> Multi-Seasonal Time Series: #> Start: 2004 1 #> Seasonal Periods: 24 168 8766 #> Data: #> [1] 484 457 450 448 444 490 autoplot(gefcom2012_load[[4]])

title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: 1001 time series M competition, taken demography, industry economics, ranging length 9 132 observations. data either non-seasonal (e.g., annual), quarterly monthly. data positive, made possibly compute mean absolute percentage errors, really reflective population real data. M1 class Mcomp time series class Mdata. function subset inherited Mcomp package can return subset specified periods, types data . See Mcomp package details.  111 series used extended comparisons 1982 M-competition can selected follows. data Mcomp Tcomp packages Mcomp class contains various information used competitions including training test portions time series. function combine_training_test combines training data test data single ts object.
code: M1 #> M-Competition data: 1001 time series  #>  #>            Type of data #> Period      DEMOGR INDUST MACRO1 MACRO2 MICRO1 MICRO2 MICRO3 Total #>   MONTHLY       75    183     64     92     10     89    104   617 #>   QUARTERLY     39     18     45     59      5     21     16   203 #>   YEARLY        30     35     30     29     16     29     12   181 #>   Total        144    236    139    180     31    139    132  1001 autoplot(M1[[7]]) subset(M1,"monthly") #> M-Competition data: 617 MONTHLY time series #>  #>          Type of data #> Period    DEMOGR INDUST MACRO1 MACRO2 MICRO1 MICRO2 MICRO3 #>   MONTHLY     75    183     64     92     10     89    104 subset(M1,111) #> M-Competition data: 111 time series  #>  #>            Type of data #> Period      DEMOGR INDUST MACRO1 MACRO2 MICRO1 MICRO2 MICRO3 Total #>   MONTHLY        8     21      8      9      1     10     11    68 #>   QUARTERLY      5      2      5      6      0      3      2    23 #>   YEARLY         3      4      4      3      2      3      1    20 #>   Total         16     27     17     18      3     16     14   111 m1ts <- combine_training_test(M1)

title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: time series M3 forecasting competition forecasts original participating methods stored M3 M3Forecast. M3 list 3003 series class Mcomp. series within M3 class Mdata. M3Forecast list data.frames. See Mcomp package details.
code: M3 #> M-Competition data: 3003 time series  #>  #>            Type of data #> Period      DEMOGRAPHIC FINANCE INDUSTRY MACRO MICRO OTHER Total #>   MONTHLY           111     145      334   312   474    52  1428 #>   OTHER               0      29        0     0     4   141   174 #>   QUARTERLY          57      76       83   336   204     0   756 #>   YEARLY            245      58      102    83   146    11   645 #>   Total             413     308      519   731   828   204  3003 autoplot(M3[[8]]) subset(M3, "macro") #> M-Competition data: 731 MACRO time series #>  #>            Type of data #> Period      MACRO #>   MONTHLY     312 #>   QUARTERLY   336 #>   YEARLY       83

title: Introduction to the tscompdata package
text: Data tourism forecasting competition described Athanasopoulos, Hyndman, Song Wu (2011). tourism list 1,311 series class Mcomp, individual series element class Mdata. See Tcomp package details.
